de.imise.ontomed.owl2graphml.onto

Class MainOntology

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.imise.ontomed.owl2graphml.onto.Ontology
      • de.imise.ontomed.owl2graphml.onto.MainOntology

  • public class MainOntology
extends Ontology
    Instances of this class provide a method to covert an ontology to GraphML. There are many properties to manipulate the resulting GraphML. Those properties can be set with respective methods.

    • Constructor Detail

      • MainOntology

        public MainOntology(org.semanticweb.owlapi.model.OWLOntology ontology,
                    java.lang.String startClassIri,
                    java.lang.String taxonomyDirection,
                    int taxonomyDepth)
             throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Constructor for instances of this class, which can be configured to manipulate the resulting GraphML.
        Parameters:
        ontology - an OWLOntology instance
        startClassIri - IRI of a class of the ontology, which will be used as start class
        taxonomyDirection - specifies the direction to collect classes in the ontology starting from the selected start class, allowed are "up" and "down"
        taxonomyDepth - maximum depth for which classes should be included into the graph
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if an unsupported argument was given
